--- PART 4: COPART vs D^{2n} SIGN ---
Connection: copart=0 (no additive coupling) correlates with
the D^4 contribution being nonzero (3-resonance = q=3)
copart=p (additive coupling exists) correlates with
the D^4 contribution being zero (higher-q resonance)

This is because 3-resonance means a/b = 3 (multiplicatively),
which implies a+b and b-a are BOTH QNR (no zero-sum triple),
while 5-resonance or higher allows zero-sum triples to exist.

